\mt3 Me Bukano Mabu Awokalimi Tabo  
\p Me buka ebe Fly Tabo epono bukala, ibi mabumaÍěČ ale me tabono iyaiya tanalo keyakeyapino Baibolo bukane obaÍěČmidalimaÍěČ. EgaÍěČwalo kalakala kawonomola, me atu tetelo ale Aramia Tabo epono buka ibi mabumaÍěČ atumu kosiyodilimaÍěČ. Buka kaÍěČlaÍěČmioledawa, aÍěČmaÍěČle me bukano unu tabo ma kunu umaÍěČta, ‚ÄėGodokono Wade Tabo, Ebete Ebeno Oli Nopo Epatamo Diyatiya.‚Äô  
\p EbemaÍěČ ale aimano kawo kalakalanomo Godotamo adipatemaÍěČ, mabu ebeno nilakapo magumulo ebete ebeno ubi tanalo iyalo iyatiya me wade tanalo Tabo epatamo kosiyodilomaÍěČ. Me mabumaÍěČ 1987 ulamalo wagilimite, ebete iyaiya nanitabokobi midipi epetapino tepo magumuno woki eba wadipalatelelo ibino towetowe tabo gela tanalodo egaÍěČwalo ibino mani ikameo tanalodo atamo elawo ikaeamenaki, ale me woko nanitabonomolo kopoliyamaÍěČ.  
\p EbemaÍěČ modobola Godote me bukano woko osiyodilo tanalone kawo amama tanalonomo naÍěČlawenakomene, mabu nanitabola, ‚ÄúEbete moto ete woko osiyodiloaÍěČno, piyate ebe woko osiyodilomaÍěČ dowagelena ibaÍěČte nanitabo tanalo aÍěČkuimaÍěČnaÍěČ‚ÄĚ (Oale 127.1). EbemaÍěČ kalakala kawonomola, Godote kebe woko iyalo dowagilimiya, ebete ebe wade woko ebeno Tabo epagodolo eba osiyodilona, modobola ibaÍěČte me Igilo Buka kaÍěČlaÍěČmiole tanalodo egaÍěČwalo iyatulame tanalodo ibino nanitabokobi midi magumulo kodakodanomomaÍěČ nedaÍěČomaÍěČnaÍěČ.  
\mt3 English Preface  
\p This book is a translation of the New Testament into the Fly River dialect of the Tabo language of Papua New Guinea. It is being published simultaneously with the New Testament for the other half of the language, the speakers of the Aramia River dialect. The two dialects together presently comprise a total of about 3,400 speakers, most of whom live in villages located along the banks of the Aramia, Bamu, and Fly Rivers as well as Segero Creek.  
\p We offer thanks to God who out of love for the Tabo people determined to give them this special gift. We are grateful to Him for the many, many individuals who, by their faithfulness in prayer and giving over the years, have enabled us to complete this work. Through them God has caused this portion of His Word to become a reality for the Tabo people in their heart language.  
\p And so we dedicate this book to God for his eternal glory, for truly, ‚ÄúUnless He builds the house, its builders labour in vain‚ÄĚ (Psalm 127.1). May He use the reading and the teaching of this Book of Life to continue building His house among the Tabo people, helping them not only to grow as a church in terms of numbers, but also in an ever increasing quality of faith.  